The application shall state:
The full name, Maryland residence address, race, sex, height, weight, general physical condition, and date of birth of the applicant;
Whether the applicant previously has been refused a license to drive and, if so:
By what state or country; and
The date of and reason for the refusal;
Whether the applicant previously has been licensed to drive and, if so:
When and by what state or country; and
Whether the license ever has been suspended, revoked, or canceled and, if so, the date of and reason for the suspension, revocation, or cancellation;
Subject to the provisions of subsection (c) of this section, the applicant's Social Security number; and
Any other pertinent information that the Administration requires.

section.section:
An applicant who claims a name change by or under the common law of this State or any other state shall submit with the applicant's application the following:
An affidavit of the name by which the applicant is known and transacts business, as demonstrated by a Social Security card or record together with documents from at least 2 of the following categories:
Tax records;
Selective Service card or records;
Voter registration card or records;
Passport;
A form of identification issued by a government unit that contains a photograph of the applicant;
Baptismal certificate;
Banking records; and
Other proof of age and identity that is satisfactory to the Administration;
Any document required under subparagraph (i) of this paragraph reflecting the legal name previously given to, or used by, the applicant prior to assuming the common law name;
Any driver's license issued to the applicant in the name previously used by the applicant prior to assuming the common law name; and
A copy of the applicant's birth certificate or other proof of age and identity that is satisfactory to the Administration.
